==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scabrous
<hw>Sca"brous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>scabrosus</ets>, fr. <ets>scaber</ets> rough: cf. F. <ets>scabreux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rough to the touch, like a file; having small raised dots, scales, or points; scabby; scurfy; scaly.</def> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Harsh; unmusical.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His verse is <qex>scabrous</qex> and hobbling.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scabrousness</ent>⟦br⟧
